titleInfo.title: USA v. Watt
titleInfo.subTitle: ORDER regarding PETITION FOR OFFENDER UNDER SUPERVISION 27 as to defendant Kevin J. Watt. The court finds that the Report alleges probable cause and that the defendant should be held to answer for a final dispositional hearing before Senior Judge Strom. A final dispositional hearing will be held before Senior Judge Lyle E. Strom in Courtroom No.5. The defendant is committed to the custody of the Attorney General or his designated representative for confinement in a correctional facility. Ordered by Magistrate Judge F. A. Gossett. (1 Certified copy to USM)(MLF, )

titleInfo.title: USA v. Watt
titleInfo.subTitle: ORDER (For Revocation of Probation or Supervised Release) as to Kevin J. Watt. The defendant admitted allegations 1,4, and 5 of the Petition for Offender Under Supervision 27 and his supervised release is revoked. He iscommitted to the United States Bureau of Prisons for six (6) months. After his release from prison, he will begin a two-year term of supervised release under the same conditions previously imposed. Allegations 2 and 3 are dismissed on the motion of the government as to this defendant only as to defendant Kevin J. Watt. Ordered by Senior Judge Lyle E. Strom. (1 Certified copy to USM) (KBJ)
